Sears PurchaseProtect


















English | Español


									Welcome, sign in or register to process a claim
								


										Home | 
										Claim Status | 
										Customer Service | 
										My Profile





















						Welcome to the Help Center. Please choose a help topic below:








General Questions


How can I contact customer service?

My claim is not coming up on your web page, what should I do?

How long does it take to get my claim fulfilled?

Sears PurchaseProtect 


How do I process a claim?

Will my existing plan cover the new replacement product 
												purchased?

Does this replace my manufacturer's coverage?

What are my obligations to process my claim as quickly as 
												possible?

How do I know what accessories I will need to send in with my 
												product?

Can I purchase the Sears PurchaseProtect plan to cover 
												merchandise that I have already purchased?



How can I contact customer 
	service?

You can get immediate help during call center hours by calling 1-800-573-1088 or you can access our online customer 
service help by clicking here.


[ Back to Top ]


My claim is not coming up on your 
	web page, what should I do?

If you have a valid salescheck, showing your purchase of the Sears 
PurchaseProtect agreement, our customer service center can verify it for you. 
Please call for assistance at 1-800-573-1088.


[ Back to Top ]


How long does it take to get my 
	claim fulfilled?

The process time varies depending on your product and whether or not you need 
to process a return shipment to our returns center. It can take anywhere from 5 
- 14 business days to process your claim. If you have a specific question about 
your claim, please call customer service at 1-800-573-1088.


[ Back to Top ]


How do I process a claim?

Within the store return policy (30 or 60 days) as shown on your receipt:

a. Retain your original sales receipt as proof of purchase. Return to the Sears 
Store where you purchased your product to take advantage of Sears' store return 
policy.


After expiration of the store return policy (30 or 60 days) as shown on your receipt:

a. Do not return the defective product to the store. Returns may be made at the store 
only within the time frame indicated on your receipt. Unless you 
are exercising your product manufacturer’s warranty (and the product 
information directs you back to the Sears store), you should follow the 
directions for making a claim in your Sears PurchaseProtect contract.


b. Log on to www.searspurchaseprotect.com
to initiate your claim or register your plan. If you do not have access to a 
computer, or prefer calling, call 1-800-573-1088. A customer service associate 
will walk you through the process and can initiate the claim for you.


c. Have your original sales receipt, and purchase date. This will be required 
to make a claim.


d. We'll confirm your product defect, and verify your address. You will have 
the opportunity to download a pre-paid shipping label or have one mailed to 
you. It's important to note that products with no defect found or accidental 
damage will be returned and in that case gift card may not be issued. Please 
see Terms and Conditions for complete details.


e. Once you have the prepaid shipping label, ship the defective product or 
component to our returns processing center. Use the original product box and 
packing material if you have them. They are designed specifically for the 
transfer of your product. To expedite the process, please include all 
	accessories that came with your original purchase, including the owner's 
	manual, before sending your product to our returns center.


	Click here to view the list of common accessories

f. You'll receive a gift card for the original purchase price, including sales 
tax, by return mail. If you purchase your replacement in advance and can show 
proof of that purchase at your Sears store (by receipt number and purchase 
date) you will receive an option to receive a check rather than a gift card. In 
some cases, Sears reserves the right to ship a refurbished replacement for 
certain products that may not be in stock at your local Sears stores.


g. Use the gift card to replace your defective product with a replacement 
product of your choice at any Sears Store nationwide!


h. You are responsible for any difference between the purchase price of your 
selected replacement and the gift card. Any excess funds will be placed on a 
Sears Gift Card.


[ Back to Top ]


Will my existing plan cover the 
	new replacement product purchased?

No, the plan is designed for a one-time use and the contract is fulfilled after 
the gift card is issued (that's why the price is so low). If you use the gift 
card to replace the defective product with a replacement product of your 
choice, we recommend you purchase a new Sears PurchaseProtect Plan.


[ Back to Top ]


Does the Sears PurchaseProtect 
	plan replace my manufacturer's coverage?

No, it provides a more simplified alternative to the manufacturer's coverage. 
Most standard warranties do not provide replacement coverage. In addition, they 
often require you to ship it in for repair at your expense. Your SPP contract 
provides an advantage to replace your product in a flexible way. You are free 
to contact the manufacturer during their coverage period if you would rather 
reserve your one-time gift card replacement option for a later date within the 
term. To contact your manufacturer, please go to their web site or call them at 
the number listed in your owner’s manual.


[ Back to Top ]


What are my obligations to process 
	my claim as quickly as possible?

Your original sales transaction showing your Sears PurchaseProtect is the most 
important piece of our claims process because it proves your purchase and 
coverage. It also speeds verification. To expedite the process, please include 
	all accessories that accompanied your original purchase, including owner's 
	manual, before sending your product to our product testing center.Click here to 
	view the list of accessories, which may have accompanied your product during 
	your original purchase.


	Click here to view the list of common accessories



[ Back to Top ]


How do I know what accessories I 
	will need to send in with my product?


	Click here to view the list of common accessories, which may have come 
with your product during your original purchase.


[ Back to Top ]


Can I purchase the Sears 
	PurchaseProtect plan to cover merchandise that I have already purchased?

The Sears PurchaseProtect plan must be purchased on select eligible merchandise 
at the same time as the purchase of the merchandise to be covered at a Sears 
store or on Sears.com. The Sears PurchaseProtect plan cannot be purchased to 
cover previously purchased merchandise.


[ Back to Top ]














